cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.CR

The paper deals with the complexity of a probabilistic logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The use of probability operators and the analysis of their impact on the complexity of the logic suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also involves computational complexity theory, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
